.doc: 'Returns the binary logarithm of the argument `x`.
	log2(x) = log2((2 ** n) * ((x / 2) ** n)) =
	= log2(2 ** n) + log2((x / 2) ** n) = n + log2(q)
	n = most significant bit of x (BSR (bit scan reverse))
	q = (x / 2) ** n = (x > 1) ? (x >> n) : (x << -n)
	x > 1 <=> n - precision > 0
	log2(q) = look up from table'
